A CRM sales funnel tracks a prospect from first contact to becoming a customer and beyond. The exact stages vary by company, but a common funnel looks like this:

Stage	Description	CRM Activities	KPI
1. Lead Capture	New lead enters the system	Web forms, ads, referrals, events, imports	Number of Leads
2. Lead Qualification	Determine if the lead fits your target profile	BANT, lead scoring, discovery questions	Qualified Lead Rate
3. Initial Contact	First outreach to the lead	Calls, emails, WhatsApp, SMS	Contact Rate
4. Needs Assessment	Understand business requirements and pain points	Discovery meetings, surveys, demos	Meeting Conversion Rate
5. Opportunity Creation	Qualified lead becomes a sales opportunity	Create deal/opportunity record	Opportunities Created
6. Solution Presentation	Demonstrate product/service value	Product demo, proposal, presentation	Demo-to-Proposal Rate
7. Proposal/Quotation	Send pricing and commercial terms	Generate quote, proposal tracking	Proposal Acceptance Rate
8. Negotiation	Handle objections and finalize terms	Follow-ups, contract revisions	Negotiation Success Rate
9. Closing (Won/Lost)	Deal is won or lost	Contract signing, payment collection	Close Rate
10. Onboarding	Customer implementation begins	Training, setup, project kickoff	Time to Go-Live
11. Customer Success	Ensure customer receives value	Support, health checks, reviews	Customer Satisfaction
12. Upsell & Renewal	Expand revenue from existing customers	Cross-sell, upsell, renewals	Customer Lifetime Value

